WEBVTT

00:02.330 --> 00:03.960
Ugh.

00:03.960 --> 00:06.960
All I do is bake,
cut, jar, repeat.

00:06.960 --> 00:09.460
I honestly can't remember
my life before lasagna.

00:09.460 --> 00:10.380
It was us.

00:10.380 --> 00:11.380
You're right.

00:11.380 --> 00:12.670
I blacked it out.

00:12.670 --> 00:13.830
You know,
if you need a break,

00:13.830 --> 00:15.250
my college is doing
a walking tour

00:15.250 --> 00:16.580
of the first
Connecticut Post Office.

00:16.580 --> 00:17.790
I could see
if there's still tickets.

00:17.790 --> 00:20.620
I guarantee you
there's still tickets.

00:20.620 --> 00:21.750
Trip's gonna be here
in a couple minutes,

00:21.750 --> 00:23.040
so just waffles to go.

00:23.040 --> 00:24.830
Syrup on the side.
I don't want them to get soggy.

00:24.830 --> 00:26.920
Greg, did you hear that?
She ordered waffles.

00:26.920 --> 00:28.880
Huh. She didn't even
want to hear the specials.
Mnh-mnh.

00:28.880 --> 00:31.290
I just want breakfast to go.
I don't see the big deal.

00:31.290 --> 00:33.290
The big deal is
you always think of yourself.

00:33.290 --> 00:35.580
I'm working my ass off to help
support this family.

00:35.580 --> 00:38.380
Okay, okay. I didn't mean to
trigger a mom rant.

00:38.380 --> 00:39.880
Nobody mention paper straws.

00:39.880 --> 00:41.540
Ugh!
They're terrible!

00:41.540 --> 00:43.210
They get all mushy
and fall apart.

00:43.210 --> 00:44.250
And what about milkshakes?

00:44.250 --> 00:46.460
You can't even drink
a milkshake anymore.

00:46.460 --> 00:47.460
What are you doing?

00:47.460 --> 00:48.750
Making things worse.
[ Sighs ]

00:50.460 --> 00:52.170
Hey babe, did you get your
admissions letter yet?

00:52.170 --> 00:54.170
No, but I hope it comes soon
and I get accepted

00:54.170 --> 00:55.460
so I can get out
of this prison.

00:55.460 --> 00:56.500
Taylor, come on.

00:56.500 --> 00:58.250
Sorry.
It's not a prison.

00:58.250 --> 01:00.040
Prisoners
get breakfast.
Ugh.

01:00.040 --> 01:02.000
Babe, if you do get in,
you'll move away from me.

01:02.000 --> 01:03.540
That letter
could change everything.

01:03.540 --> 01:05.080
Let's not worry about it
until it happens.

01:05.080 --> 01:06.460
You're right.

01:06.460 --> 01:08.750
We will paint that bridge
when we walk over it.

01:08.750 --> 01:11.120
We'll paint it then.
We'll paint it together.

01:11.120 --> 01:12.830
Oliver, we're leaving.

01:12.830 --> 01:14.920
If my admissions letter
from Carnegie Mellon comes,

01:14.920 --> 01:15.880
don't open it.

01:18.830 --> 01:20.040
You know,
Trip is right.

01:20.040 --> 01:21.500
[ Door closes ]

01:21.500 --> 01:23.500
If she gets in,
it is gonna change everything.

01:23.500 --> 01:26.380
I know. The first year's tuition
is $56,000.

01:26.380 --> 01:27.120
Ugh.

01:29.920 --> 01:31.540
We've talked
about this.

01:31.540 --> 01:34.000
You can't kill me so you can
cash in my life insurance.

01:34.000 --> 01:35.460
It's illegal,
and you'll get caught.

01:35.460 --> 01:37.710
Oh, I would not get caught.

01:37.710 --> 01:40.420
I would not get caught.

01:40.420 --> 01:41.420
♪♪

01:47.580 --> 01:52.580
♪♪

01:52.580 --> 01:53.670
Kate!

01:53.670 --> 01:55.920
Nice mustache,
mid-puberty Justin Bieber.

01:55.920 --> 01:57.580
I'll take it.
[ Sighs ]

01:57.580 --> 01:59.040
That dude's yoked now.

01:59.040 --> 02:00.250
Mm.
Greg's in his office.

02:02.670 --> 02:04.540
[ Air hisses ]

02:04.540 --> 02:06.540
[ Paintball gun firing ]
Greg: Ow! Aah! Gah! Oh, ow!

02:06.540 --> 02:07.920
Lonnie: [ Laughs ]
Lonnie, come on!

02:07.920 --> 02:09.830
[ Sighs ]
Oh!

02:11.290 --> 02:13.330
What am I doing,
wasting my time

02:13.330 --> 02:15.170
writing a book about
this social media half-wit

02:15.170 --> 02:16.750
who contributes nothing of value
to our society

02:16.750 --> 02:18.420
or the world in general?

02:18.420 --> 02:20.500
You're selling out so you can
send your daughter to college.

02:20.500 --> 02:22.460
Right.

02:22.460 --> 02:25.790
Anna-Kat, you're gonna be late
for school!

02:25.790 --> 02:26.750
I'm missing health class.

02:26.750 --> 02:28.080
It's fine.

02:28.080 --> 02:29.420
I don't need Ms. Shineburg
to explain

02:29.420 --> 02:31.000
why I'm starting to get B.O.

02:31.000 --> 02:33.170
Hey, I need you to buy
a hundred boxes

02:33.170 --> 02:35.170
of Wildflower Girl cookies
from me.

02:35.170 --> 02:36.710
It's the last weekend
to sell,

02:36.710 --> 02:38.460
and I'm not even close
to my goal.

02:38.460 --> 02:39.620
Oh, sure.

02:39.620 --> 02:42.500
What's that, $500?
I don't have any cash.

02:42.500 --> 02:43.790
Grab a handful of diamonds
from the vault.

02:43.790 --> 02:45.830
We're regular people,
Anna-Kat.

02:45.830 --> 02:47.170
We live month-to-month.

02:47.170 --> 02:48.960
We can't just throw money
at problems.

02:48.960 --> 02:51.500
Fine. I guess
I won't win the trip.

02:51.500 --> 02:53.960
Wait.
What trip?

02:53.960 --> 02:56.000
The Wildflower Girl
who sells the most cookies

02:56.000 --> 02:59.380
gets an all-expense paid
family trip to Hollywood.

02:59.380 --> 03:03.790
I haven't been on a vacation
since I gave birth to you.

03:03.790 --> 03:06.500
Oh, two weeks of bed rest
at a Kaiser, baby!

03:06.500 --> 03:08.420
The vacation includes
spa treatments,

03:08.420 --> 03:10.170
tickets to
a game-show taping,

03:10.170 --> 03:11.960
and the hotel
has a kids' club,

03:11.960 --> 03:14.670
which means after we enjoy
our complimentary breakfast,

03:14.670 --> 03:17.000
you won't see me until
our complimentary dinner.

03:17.000 --> 03:19.290
[ Gasps ]
Let's sell some cookies!

03:19.290 --> 03:21.460
[ School bell rings ]

03:21.460 --> 03:23.620
Got a little
surprise for you.

03:23.620 --> 03:24.960
[ Gasps ]

03:24.960 --> 03:27.120
Two tickets to
the Winter Festival?

03:27.120 --> 03:29.500
Aww! That's where
we had our first date.

03:29.500 --> 03:31.380
With you maybe going to college
in a few months,

03:31.380 --> 03:33.250
I thought it'd be fun to
remember where it all started.

03:33.250 --> 03:35.620
It's also where
we had our first kiss.

03:35.620 --> 03:37.920
And where we had
our first funnel cake.

03:37.920 --> 03:39.040
[ Chuckles ]

03:39.040 --> 03:40.580
Okay,
I have to come clean.

03:40.580 --> 03:41.830
I'd had funnel cake
before,

03:41.830 --> 03:43.380
but I swear
it meant nothing to me!

03:43.380 --> 03:45.000
[ Laughs ]

03:45.000 --> 03:47.380
I can't believe that's the guy
who called Teen Help Line

03:47.380 --> 03:49.040
saying he wanted
to off himself.

03:49.040 --> 03:51.580
Yeah.
It doesn't make any sense.

03:51.580 --> 03:53.420
He's popular,
he's lettered in three sports,

03:53.420 --> 03:55.080
all the girls like him.

03:55.080 --> 03:56.250
And a teacher
actually resigned

03:56.250 --> 03:57.750
because she
fell in love with him.

03:57.750 --> 04:00.420
How cool is that?

04:00.420 --> 04:02.460
I just need to
get him to open up,

04:02.460 --> 04:04.460
but I can't
just approach him,

04:04.460 --> 04:06.460
because Teen Help Line
is confidential.

04:06.460 --> 04:08.540
I'm not even
supposed to know who he is.

04:08.540 --> 04:10.500
I have to get him
to call back.

04:10.500 --> 04:11.500
But how?

04:11.500 --> 04:13.670
I have no idea.

04:13.670 --> 04:15.000
Dude, I'm sorry.
I'm hungry.

04:15.000 --> 04:16.540
My blood shugie's muy low.

04:16.540 --> 04:19.500
♪♪

04:19.500 --> 04:21.670
Obviously, Greg and I
hope that she gets in,

04:21.670 --> 04:24.170
but we just aren't sure how
we're gonna pay for it.

04:24.170 --> 04:26.170
Katie, I can't fix
your poorness.

04:26.170 --> 04:27.420
Okay?

04:27.420 --> 04:29.000
And thinking about it
is making it difficult

04:29.000 --> 04:30.580
for me to enjoy
my frittata.
Ugh.

04:30.580 --> 04:31.880
Why don't you give me
something easier?

04:31.880 --> 04:34.330
Like, what's with
the little child of yours

04:34.330 --> 04:36.460
and, um,
her cake project?

04:36.460 --> 04:38.380
You mean Anna-Kat
and the cookies?
Yes.

04:38.380 --> 04:40.080
She's trying to
sell enough boxes

04:40.080 --> 04:41.420
to win a trip
to Hollywood,

04:41.420 --> 04:42.670
but it's hard to compete

04:42.670 --> 04:44.540
when all the other girls
buy their victories.

04:44.540 --> 04:47.290
Ugh. All roads
lead back to poorness.

04:47.290 --> 04:49.380
So, if you can't outspend them,
outthink them.

04:49.380 --> 04:51.330
Dust off your marketing degree
and sell some cookies.

04:51.330 --> 04:52.540
Oh, we are.

04:52.540 --> 04:54.000
We are going to hit up
the grocery stores,

04:54.000 --> 04:55.580
walk the neighborhoods --

04:55.580 --> 04:57.960
Katie, that's how they sold
cookies in the old days.

04:57.960 --> 05:00.330
Make a video and hit
social media like Lonnie does.

05:00.330 --> 05:02.580
Oooh, that's good.
Mm-hmm.

05:02.580 --> 05:03.960
Hey, um, by the way,

05:03.960 --> 05:05.580
is Lonnie single?

05:05.580 --> 05:07.290
Doris.

05:07.290 --> 05:08.290
I just saw that show
"Mrs. Fletcher,"

05:08.290 --> 05:09.290
and I got me some ideas.

05:09.290 --> 05:10.620
Mnh-mnh, no.

05:10.620 --> 05:12.750
♪♪

05:12.750 --> 05:13.920
You ready?

05:15.380 --> 05:17.000
You know, sometimes
I have a hard time

05:17.000 --> 05:19.290
talking my problems through.

05:19.290 --> 05:21.830
Maybe there's something
on this bulletin board

05:21.830 --> 05:23.580
that could help us.

05:23.580 --> 05:25.380
Oooh, someone's selling
Wimbledon tickets.

05:26.880 --> 05:28.210
If you're really
feeling sad,

05:28.210 --> 05:29.830
you should call
Teen Help Line.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.080
It's anonymous,

05:31.080 --> 05:32.880
and it's not some adult
who doesn't get it.

05:32.880 --> 05:35.420
It's teens
talking to teens.

05:35.420 --> 05:38.460
The best time to call is Tuesday
between 5:00 and 10:00 p.m.

05:38.460 --> 05:40.330
Hey, Jacob!
Wait up!

05:40.330 --> 05:41.960
Damn.

05:41.960 --> 05:42.960
I don't know
if he heard me.

05:42.960 --> 05:44.540
If it makes you feel
any better,

05:44.540 --> 05:46.120
I'm going to Wimbledon!

05:46.120 --> 05:48.250
♪♪

05:48.250 --> 05:49.620
When I shot my buddy Turd

05:49.620 --> 05:51.330
in the nads
with a paintball gun,

05:51.330 --> 05:53.120
I got to
one million followers.

05:53.120 --> 05:55.790
But the real turning point,
which got me to 35 mil,

05:55.790 --> 05:58.290
was when I jumped off my garage
dressed as a bird

05:58.290 --> 05:59.790
and I broke
both my ankles.

05:59.790 --> 06:01.620
I was like, "Cawww!"

06:01.620 --> 06:03.500
And then I was like,
"Aaaaaah!"

06:03.500 --> 06:05.000
[ Laughs ]

06:05.000 --> 06:06.960
Fascinating.

06:06.960 --> 06:08.960
Do you ever think you could be
doing something with your fame

06:08.960 --> 06:10.120
to make a difference
in the world?

06:11.710 --> 06:13.460
What do you mean?

06:13.460 --> 06:14.960
I mean, you have a platform

06:14.960 --> 06:17.120
which reaches
millions of young people.

06:17.120 --> 06:18.580
You could have
a real impact.

06:18.580 --> 06:21.210
I think if we're gonna be
writing a book about you,

06:21.210 --> 06:23.460
we need to be saying
something more substantial.

06:23.460 --> 06:25.880
Maybe you're right.
I'll give it some thought.

06:27.120 --> 06:28.790
Hey, guys,
if you like what you see,

06:28.790 --> 06:31.500
remember to smash
that like button.

06:31.500 --> 06:34.170
Lonnie,
are you filming this?
Yeah.

06:34.170 --> 06:35.750
It's my new
video series called

06:35.750 --> 06:38.290
"Deep Talks with
Professor Badonkadonk."

06:38.290 --> 06:41.210
For the last time,
my ass isn't that big.

06:41.210 --> 06:43.080
These are thick-ribbed
corduroys.

06:45.750 --> 06:48.330
I'm heading to the edge of
the driveway to sell cookies.

06:48.330 --> 06:49.790
The days of old-school selling
are over.

06:49.790 --> 06:52.330
We are going to shoot a video
and make it go viral.

06:53.620 --> 06:54.830
Can I have 100 bucks?

06:54.830 --> 06:57.250
Is there a rich person
standing behind me?

06:57.250 --> 06:59.210
I want to spring for dinner
at Winter Fest tomorrow tonight.

06:59.210 --> 07:00.330
Trip got the tickets,

07:00.330 --> 07:01.620
and I thought it'd be
a nice gesture.

07:01.620 --> 07:03.380
Aw, babe,
you don't have to do that.

07:03.380 --> 07:04.580
She's not going to do that.

07:04.580 --> 07:06.080
I don't see the problem.

07:06.080 --> 07:08.420
You have your own company,
and Dad is writing some book.

07:08.420 --> 07:09.580
For now,
all the money that I make

07:09.580 --> 07:11.120
goes right back
into the business.

07:11.120 --> 07:13.790
And your dad doesn't get paid
until his book is published.

07:13.790 --> 07:15.620
All you guys do
is say no.

07:15.620 --> 07:17.120
That is not true.

07:17.120 --> 07:19.380
Sometimes I say
"I've got to think about it,"

07:19.380 --> 07:21.080
then I say no.
[ Door opens ]

07:21.080 --> 07:23.290
What's going in here?
I'm trying to work.
It's your daughter.

07:23.290 --> 07:25.040
Despite our
mediocre-at-best efforts,

07:25.040 --> 07:26.710
she has turned into
a spoiled brat.

07:26.710 --> 07:28.500
Ugh!
I am so sick of this!

07:28.500 --> 07:29.750
I can't wait to move out
and go to college!

07:29.750 --> 07:31.210
I can wait.

07:31.210 --> 07:32.830
You don't even know
if you're getting in yet.

07:32.830 --> 07:34.420
You're about to
find out.

07:34.420 --> 07:37.540
The letter from
Carnegie Mellon came.

07:37.540 --> 07:40.040
And Mom, here's another warning
from the library.

07:40.040 --> 07:42.040
You've gotta return
"Gone Girl."

07:42.040 --> 07:44.080
I will finish
in my own damn time.

07:49.170 --> 07:51.750
♪♪

07:51.750 --> 07:52.830
Are you going to
open it?

07:52.830 --> 07:53.880
Yeah, open it.

07:53.880 --> 07:55.170
Not now.

07:55.170 --> 07:57.040
If I get in,
Trip will be sad.

07:57.040 --> 07:58.710
But if I don't get in,
then I'll be sad.

07:58.710 --> 08:00.880
Either way, our night at
the festival is ruined.

08:00.880 --> 08:02.500
You know what?

08:02.500 --> 08:04.620
I'll leave it here
and open it later.

08:04.620 --> 08:06.920
If I don't know,
I don't have to worry about it.

08:06.920 --> 08:08.920
Are you sure, babe?

08:08.920 --> 08:11.380
Patience is a dish
best served cold.

08:11.380 --> 08:13.620
It is, babe.
It's best served cold.

08:13.620 --> 08:16.330
[ Sighs ]

08:16.330 --> 08:17.620
Nope.
It's Trip.

08:17.620 --> 08:19.210
[ Door opens ]

08:19.210 --> 08:20.710
Oh, sorry, I keep a running tab
in my head

08:20.710 --> 08:22.460
of which one of them
is dumber.

08:22.460 --> 08:23.710
Ohh.

08:25.000 --> 08:28.460
We came to you because you are
the expert for Internet videos.

08:28.460 --> 08:31.120
Well, I like to start
by brainstorming ideas.
Mm-hmm.

08:31.120 --> 08:32.500
Franklin, say the first thing
that comes to mind.

08:32.500 --> 08:34.620
Uh, dragons.
Balloons.

08:34.620 --> 08:36.750
Mermaids. Volcanos.
The movie "Soapdish" --

08:36.750 --> 08:38.250
Okay, good work.
Take a break.

08:38.250 --> 08:40.000
Anna-Kat?

08:40.000 --> 08:41.620
How about
a claymation video?

08:41.620 --> 08:43.960
Do you even know
how to do that?
No.

08:43.960 --> 08:45.500
Okay, good work.
Take a break.

08:46.580 --> 08:48.290
Kate.

08:48.290 --> 08:50.670
Dragons. Balloons.
Mermaids.

08:50.670 --> 08:52.290
[ Anna-Kat laughs ]

08:52.290 --> 08:54.290
[ Muffled ] I fit
14 cookies into my mouth.

08:54.290 --> 08:56.830
How many cookies
can you fit in your mouth?

08:56.830 --> 08:58.540
This kid's a genius.

08:58.540 --> 09:01.120
[ Muffled ]
Hi, I'm Anna-Kat Otto,

09:01.120 --> 09:03.500
and I have 10 cookies
in my mouth.

09:03.500 --> 09:05.040
Can you beat me?

09:05.040 --> 09:06.920
Take my Wildflower Girls
Cookie Challenge

09:06.920 --> 09:07.670
and find out.

09:07.670 --> 09:09.210
[ Ding! ]

09:09.210 --> 09:11.120
Order your cookies
under Anna-Kat Otto

09:11.120 --> 09:12.960
on the Wildflower Girls website

09:12.960 --> 09:14.960
and challenge your friends.

09:14.960 --> 09:16.580
It's official.

09:16.580 --> 09:18.880
The Wildflower Girls Cookie
Challenge has launched.

09:18.880 --> 09:20.620
Awesome.

09:20.620 --> 09:22.500
But maybe we should re-edit
to include a link to my podcast,

09:22.500 --> 09:24.170
"Getting Frank
With Franklin."

09:24.170 --> 09:25.580
Guess who next week's
guest is?

09:25.580 --> 09:27.420
Me.
It's always me.

09:29.170 --> 09:30.540
♪♪

09:30.540 --> 09:31.540
Trip:
This is great.

09:31.540 --> 09:32.750
I don't know about you,

09:32.750 --> 09:33.670
but I'm not thinking about
that letter at all.

09:33.670 --> 09:35.080
What letter?

09:35.080 --> 09:36.920
The letter
from Carnegie Mellon.

09:36.920 --> 09:38.170
Oh, I know.

09:38.170 --> 09:39.500
I was just pretending
I didn't know

09:39.500 --> 09:41.120
because that's how little
I'm thinking about it.

09:41.120 --> 09:42.920
You're such
a good actress.

09:42.920 --> 09:44.330
You're totally getting in.

09:44.330 --> 09:45.920
Stop!
Let's just keep having fun

09:45.920 --> 09:47.380
and not think about
Carnegie Mellon.

09:47.380 --> 09:49.710
Hi! Uh, what's your
flavor of the day?

09:49.710 --> 09:50.710
Melon.

09:50.710 --> 09:52.500
Oh, God.

09:52.500 --> 09:56.080
[ Telephones ringing,
indistinct chatter ]

09:56.080 --> 09:57.500
Oh, hey, Deborah.
How was your weekend?

09:57.500 --> 09:59.670
It was good,
but challenging.

09:59.670 --> 10:01.580
Okay.
Great.

10:01.580 --> 10:04.710
I got into a fight with my
mother about boundaries.

10:04.710 --> 10:07.290
She doesn't want me stopping by
her apartment anymore.

10:07.290 --> 10:09.620
Okay. Well, it sounds like
you worked through it.

10:09.620 --> 10:10.750
Actually, I didn't.

10:10.750 --> 10:11.880
It's just,
there's all this stuff,

10:11.880 --> 10:13.080
all this pressure,
you know? I mean --

10:13.080 --> 10:15.880
Teen Help Line. Please have
a lengthy problem.

10:15.880 --> 10:17.710
Will: Hey, man. I called
and talked to you last week.

10:17.710 --> 10:20.620
Hey!
I mean, hey.

10:20.620 --> 10:21.790
I'm glad you called back.

10:21.790 --> 10:23.170
Yeah.

10:24.790 --> 10:26.210
Maybe this was a mistake.

10:26.210 --> 10:27.920
No, no,
it's good you called.

10:27.920 --> 10:29.580
Is everything okay?

10:29.580 --> 10:31.170
I just feel like I have to
tell someone, you know?

10:31.170 --> 10:32.540
Y-- For sure.

10:32.540 --> 10:33.670
This is a safe space,

10:33.670 --> 10:35.120
so you can say
whatever you want.

10:37.380 --> 10:39.040
Hello?
You still there?

10:39.040 --> 10:42.120
Yeah.
Yeah, I'm still here.

10:42.120 --> 10:44.790
I just never
said this out loud before

10:44.790 --> 10:47.880
[Exhales sharply]
to myself or anyone.

10:49.080 --> 10:51.790
But, um...

10:51.790 --> 10:56.330
Uh...

10:56.330 --> 10:57.670
I think I'm gay.

10:57.670 --> 11:00.710
I mean...
No -- [ Inhales sharply ]

11:00.710 --> 11:03.580
I'm gay. Um, I'm gay.

11:03.580 --> 11:06.080
That was great.

11:06.080 --> 11:07.620
You did great.

11:07.620 --> 11:09.330
I can't believe
I just said that.

11:09.330 --> 11:11.500
You know, I know what
a big deal this is for you,

11:11.500 --> 11:14.670
but you're not alone.

11:14.670 --> 11:16.500
There are a lot of teens
who have gone through this

11:16.500 --> 11:19.880
and come out the other side
just fine.

11:19.880 --> 11:22.170
And they're not popular
football players like you.

11:22.170 --> 11:23.580
How do you know
I play football?

11:23.580 --> 11:25.960
Uh, I-I don't.

11:25.960 --> 11:27.500
It says here in the script.

11:27.500 --> 11:29.580
I say, "You're
a football player" to guys

11:29.580 --> 11:31.710
and "You're
a volleyball player" to girls.

11:31.710 --> 11:33.080
I thought this was
a national hotline.

11:33.080 --> 11:34.880
It's local?
Do you go to my school?

11:34.880 --> 11:36.120
No! Look, Will --

11:36.120 --> 11:37.210
You know who I am?!

11:37.210 --> 11:39.040
Uhhh...
You're that kid.

11:39.040 --> 11:40.540
You're that kid
by the bulletin board!

11:40.540 --> 11:42.330
You don't have to worry.
I'm not gonna tell anybody.

11:42.330 --> 11:44.500
Yeah,
I'll make sure of that.

11:44.500 --> 11:45.750
Hello? Will?

11:45.750 --> 11:47.040
I-I mean,
anonymous caller?

11:47.040 --> 11:48.710
[ Sighs ]

11:50.500 --> 11:52.710
Can I have a pretzel?

11:52.710 --> 11:54.040
Sorry, honey.

11:54.040 --> 11:56.170
She wants a pretzel.
Just let her.

11:56.170 --> 11:57.500
Did you hear that?

11:57.500 --> 12:00.210
The mom said, "Let her."
As in "admissions letter"?

12:00.210 --> 12:02.170
[ Sighs ] We're clearly
not gonna have any fun.

12:02.170 --> 12:03.960
Let's just go home,
open the letter,

12:03.960 --> 12:05.380
and get it over with.
"Letter."

12:05.380 --> 12:06.500
You just said "letter"!
There it is again!

12:06.500 --> 12:08.290
[ Scoffs ]

12:08.290 --> 12:11.210
[ Laughs ]
Ow!

12:11.210 --> 12:12.210
Ah!

12:12.210 --> 12:14.040
You know that phrase
"It never gets old"?

12:14.040 --> 12:15.880
That does not apply here.

12:15.880 --> 12:19.000
Oh, I actually took your advice
about making an impact.

12:19.000 --> 12:20.880
I shot a video where
I handed out money to people.

12:20.880 --> 12:22.460
Oh.

12:22.460 --> 12:24.380
It wasn't real money,
they were Lonnie Bucks,

12:24.380 --> 12:26.210
but they are redeemable
on my website

12:26.210 --> 12:27.920
for some sick merch, bro.

12:27.920 --> 12:30.960
That's 10 million
Lonnie Bucks.

12:30.960 --> 12:33.080
You're halfway to a T-shirt
with paintball splats on it.

12:33.080 --> 12:35.040
I already have six of those.

12:35.040 --> 12:37.080
Lonnie, I appreciate
that you're trying,

12:37.080 --> 12:38.420
but making a difference

12:38.420 --> 12:40.080
means doing something
for someone else

12:40.080 --> 12:41.620
that doesn't
benefit yourself.

12:41.620 --> 12:43.420
[ Scoffs ]

12:43.420 --> 12:45.420
I don't get
your generation.

12:45.420 --> 12:49.960
♪♪

12:49.960 --> 12:51.540
We came for more cookies!

12:51.540 --> 12:53.290
Yep.
We sold out again.

12:53.290 --> 12:55.880
I saw your video.
So creative.

12:55.880 --> 12:57.670
I guess when you have
no other resources,

12:57.670 --> 12:59.250
you have to use
the ol' noodle, huh?

12:59.250 --> 13:00.710
[ Chuckles ]
Mm.

13:00.710 --> 13:03.080
I took your cookie challenge,
Anna-Kat.

13:03.080 --> 13:05.170
I hope you win.

13:05.170 --> 13:07.710
You're not going to,
though.

13:07.710 --> 13:10.380
Because however many boxes
you sell,

13:10.380 --> 13:12.750
I'm going to have my dad
buy one more so I win.

13:12.750 --> 13:13.830
Why would you do that?

13:13.830 --> 13:16.420
Because my mom and I
like to win things.

13:16.420 --> 13:19.170
Right, Mom?
You got it, baby!

13:19.170 --> 13:20.790
Do you even want
that vacation?

13:20.790 --> 13:23.210
Oh, Katie.
The Los Angeles thing?

13:23.210 --> 13:25.000
[ Chuckles ]
That's not a vacation.

13:25.000 --> 13:26.830
I just have some errands
to run out there.

13:31.540 --> 13:33.420
I'm sorry, Anna-Kat.

13:33.420 --> 13:34.330
But you should be
proud of yourself.

13:34.330 --> 13:36.420
You tried to win
the contest the right way,

13:36.420 --> 13:38.540
and at the end of the day,
that's what's most important.

13:38.540 --> 13:40.330
I already know that lesson.

13:40.330 --> 13:42.420
I wanted to learn
a new lesson,

13:42.420 --> 13:44.580
the one where I work hard
and get a great trip.

13:44.580 --> 13:45.830
There'll be other trips.

13:45.830 --> 13:48.670
No.
Not really.

13:48.670 --> 13:50.120
I just wanted a real vacation

13:50.120 --> 13:52.040
before my big sister
goes away to college

13:52.040 --> 13:53.790
and changes our family
forever.

13:55.710 --> 13:57.920
Oh, sweetie.

13:57.920 --> 13:59.750
This was gonna be
our last big memory

13:59.750 --> 14:01.000
when we're all together.

14:03.500 --> 14:04.960
[ Sighs ]

14:04.960 --> 14:06.790
[ Sighs ]

14:06.790 --> 14:08.540
It's like a paintball
to your heart, right, Kate?

14:11.080 --> 14:12.580
Run.
Yep.

14:17.880 --> 14:19.380
Hey, you.
[ Car door closes ]

14:19.380 --> 14:21.210
Will, wait! I don't want to die
in a pair of Kirkland jeans.

14:21.210 --> 14:23.710
You better
keep your mouth shut.

14:23.710 --> 14:25.210
Of course.

14:25.210 --> 14:26.790
And I know this is easy
for me to say,

14:26.790 --> 14:28.960
but I don't think
it will ruin your life

14:28.960 --> 14:30.290
if people know you're gay.

14:30.290 --> 14:32.080
Will you shut up?

14:35.670 --> 14:36.920
Look, you --

14:36.920 --> 14:38.750
You don't know
what it's like.

14:38.750 --> 14:41.540
There are expectations
of me --

14:41.540 --> 14:42.790
at home, at school,

14:42.790 --> 14:44.790
with my friends
and my teammates.

14:44.790 --> 14:47.540
Yeah, and all those people
care about you.

14:47.540 --> 14:50.000
Honestly,
if you come out,

14:50.000 --> 14:52.540
I really believe
everyone will support you.

14:52.540 --> 14:54.380
You don't know
what you're talking about.

14:54.380 --> 14:56.580
Well, I guess there's only
one way for you to find out.

14:56.580 --> 14:58.830
Yeah, I guess.

14:58.830 --> 15:02.460
♪♪

15:02.460 --> 15:03.960
[ Car door opens, closes ]

15:04.920 --> 15:06.540
Trip: Hey.

15:06.540 --> 15:09.210
I know that you've been dying to
open that letter

15:09.210 --> 15:12.210
but you waited because you
didn't want to ruin our night.

15:13.880 --> 15:15.420
That's what I love
about you --

15:15.420 --> 15:18.830
you always put
other people first.

15:18.830 --> 15:21.250
I'll miss you, but...

15:21.250 --> 15:23.170
I really hope
you get in.

15:32.960 --> 15:35.920
Taylor, wait.

15:35.920 --> 15:37.380
I don't have
anything else.

15:37.380 --> 15:39.120
I've just seen that
happen a lot in movies.

15:39.120 --> 15:40.960
[ Laughs ]

15:42.790 --> 15:44.420
Oh.
How was the festival?

15:44.420 --> 15:45.920
Uh, not great.

15:45.920 --> 15:47.040
No matter how hard we tried,

15:47.040 --> 15:49.460
we couldn't stop
thinking about the letter.

15:49.460 --> 15:51.670
[ Sighs ]

15:51.670 --> 15:54.250
I'm gonna take this to my room
and open it alone.

15:59.620 --> 16:01.880
I suppose we should
probably talk about

16:01.880 --> 16:04.670
how we're gonna pay for
Carnegie Mellon if she gets in.

16:04.670 --> 16:06.880
Obviously, there's no way
we can afford this.

16:06.880 --> 16:08.080
[ Sighs ]

16:08.080 --> 16:09.380
Maybe your business
will take off

16:09.380 --> 16:10.750
and my book
will be a success?

16:10.750 --> 16:12.040
That's at least
a year away.

16:12.040 --> 16:14.460
How are we going to pay for it
in the meantime?

16:14.460 --> 16:16.040
I do have
10 million Lonnie Bucks.

16:16.040 --> 16:17.830
[ Groans ]

16:17.830 --> 16:19.670
She's our kid.

16:19.670 --> 16:21.330
I guess
we'll figure it out.

16:21.330 --> 16:22.710
We'll just work
until we die.

16:22.710 --> 16:24.380
And there's that lady
at the grocery store

16:24.380 --> 16:25.620
who said she'd pay anything
to have my hair.

16:28.580 --> 16:30.330
I really hope she gets in.

16:30.330 --> 16:31.620
Me too.

16:35.420 --> 16:36.790
Well?

16:36.790 --> 16:38.920
They said no.

16:38.920 --> 16:41.790
Oh.
Oh, sweetie.

16:41.790 --> 16:43.210
I'm so sorry.

16:43.210 --> 16:44.790
It is their loss.

16:44.790 --> 16:46.330
Your audition tape
was amazing.

16:46.330 --> 16:48.120
You can re-apply
next year, right?

16:48.120 --> 16:49.540
Yeah.
I guess.

16:49.540 --> 16:51.250
I know how much
you wanted this.

16:51.250 --> 16:52.830
If it's any consolation,

16:52.830 --> 16:54.620
I couldn't really wear
a college sweatshirt

16:54.620 --> 16:57.120
that said "Carnegie Mellon"
with these.

16:57.120 --> 17:01.540
♪♪

17:01.540 --> 17:05.000
Hey, do you have something
to tell me?

17:05.000 --> 17:08.710
No. Do you have something
to tell me?

17:08.710 --> 17:10.880
Mom and Dad said you didn't get
into Carnegie Mellon.

17:10.880 --> 17:12.540
Why'd you lie?

17:12.540 --> 17:13.920
What are you
talking about?

17:13.920 --> 17:15.420
I steamed open
your admissions letter,

17:15.420 --> 17:16.620
read it,
and sealed it back up.

17:16.620 --> 17:18.250
What?!

17:18.250 --> 17:20.250
I open all the important mail
that comes to the house.

17:20.250 --> 17:22.170
I'm still hoping my real parents
are trying to find me.

17:22.170 --> 17:24.290
Oliver!
I don't understand.

17:24.290 --> 17:25.830
You got in.
This is your dream.

17:27.460 --> 17:28.290
[ Sighs ]

17:30.540 --> 17:33.080
Trip told me that
I always put other people first,

17:33.080 --> 17:34.210
but you know what?

17:34.210 --> 17:35.460
I haven't been,

17:35.460 --> 17:37.420
especially with
Mom and Dad.

17:37.420 --> 17:38.750
I overheard them
talking about

17:38.750 --> 17:40.250
how they can't afford
college right now.

17:40.250 --> 17:42.500
So, I put them first.

17:42.500 --> 17:45.080
I'm gonna tell Carnegie Mellon
I'll come next year.

17:45.080 --> 17:46.580
And in the meantime,

17:46.580 --> 17:49.540
I'll get a job
and help them pay for it.

17:49.540 --> 17:53.120
Now, do you have something
to tell me?

17:53.120 --> 17:54.290
What are you
talking about?

17:54.290 --> 17:55.460
Your new
Instagram account.

17:55.460 --> 17:57.790
What?

17:57.790 --> 18:00.500
"Hey, everybody,
it's Oliver Otto.

18:00.500 --> 18:04.250
I got some advice today,
and I've decided to take it.

18:04.250 --> 18:06.330
It's time the world knows
the real me.

18:06.330 --> 18:08.120
I'm gay."

18:08.120 --> 18:10.460
It's everywhere.

18:10.460 --> 18:11.580
Oh...

18:11.580 --> 18:13.620
A kid from our school
called Teen Help Line

18:13.620 --> 18:16.080
and told me he was gay,
but he's afraid to come out.

18:16.080 --> 18:18.290
I let it slip
that I knew who he was.

18:18.290 --> 18:19.790
He must be doing this
preemptively

18:19.790 --> 18:21.080
in case I was gonna
out him.

18:21.080 --> 18:23.710
So, you're not gay?

18:23.710 --> 18:25.210
No.

18:25.210 --> 18:27.000
Are you gonna
post something denying it?

18:29.250 --> 18:30.540
No.

18:30.540 --> 18:32.120
Well, what about
everyone at school?

18:32.120 --> 18:33.790
Hopefully they'll be
cool with it,

18:33.790 --> 18:35.500
just like I told him
they would be.

18:35.500 --> 18:37.330
You think?

18:37.330 --> 18:39.380
I guess we're gonna
find out.

18:39.380 --> 18:42.210
[ Chuckles ] Look at you
being a good person.

18:42.210 --> 18:43.880
You too.
I know!

18:43.880 --> 18:45.620
What is happening to us?

18:45.620 --> 18:46.790
I think we're letting
Mom and Dad's

18:46.790 --> 18:49.460
homespun middle-class values
corrupt us.

18:49.460 --> 18:50.830
Damn them.

18:50.830 --> 18:53.420
♪♪

18:53.420 --> 18:55.750
Am I allowed to boo
when they announce
Paris as the winner?

18:55.750 --> 18:57.170
Of course, honey.

18:57.170 --> 18:58.380
But pretend to be
tying your shoe

18:58.380 --> 18:59.460
so they don't know
where it's coming from.

19:01.380 --> 19:03.040
Okay, Wildflower Girls.

19:03.040 --> 19:05.250
The moment is finally here.

19:05.250 --> 19:08.040
Time to announce
the top three sellers!

19:08.040 --> 19:10.790
In third place,
with 112 boxes sold,

19:10.790 --> 19:13.250
Elaine Johnson!

19:13.250 --> 19:14.750
[ Chuckles ]

19:14.750 --> 19:18.960
And in second place,
with 642 boxes sold, Paris!

19:18.960 --> 19:20.750
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:20.750 --> 19:22.380
Wait. No, what?

19:22.380 --> 19:23.830
That -- That's --
That's not right.

19:23.830 --> 19:26.170
That should say first place.
Um...

19:26.170 --> 19:27.830
And in first...

19:27.830 --> 19:33.170
With 87,416 boxes sold,
Anna-Kat Otto?

19:33.170 --> 19:35.790
[ All gasp ]

19:36.830 --> 19:38.420
[ Applause ]

19:38.420 --> 19:40.420
[ Laughs ]
What?

19:40.420 --> 19:41.920
How did this happen?

19:41.920 --> 19:46.040
Aaaaand 35!

19:46.040 --> 19:47.460
I took the Anna-Kat Otto

19:47.460 --> 19:48.880
Wildflower Girls Cookie
Challenge,

19:48.880 --> 19:51.250
and so should you!

19:51.250 --> 19:53.330
[ Laughs ]

19:53.330 --> 19:54.750
Click the link right here

19:54.750 --> 19:56.380
to get your own cookies
from Anna-Kat.

19:56.380 --> 19:58.380
And for every box you guys buy,

19:58.380 --> 20:00.920
I'll donate $5
to a local food pantry.

20:00.920 --> 20:04.460
Let's make a difference!

20:04.460 --> 20:06.710
Whoa, that's awesome,
Lonnie!

20:06.710 --> 20:07.710
When did you post that?

20:07.710 --> 20:09.540
About an hour ago.

20:09.540 --> 20:11.120
I saw how much it meant
to Anna-Kat

20:11.120 --> 20:12.580
to win that vacation
for your family.

20:12.580 --> 20:14.330
And I figured
the food pantry thing

20:14.330 --> 20:15.960
was a good way to
help the community.

20:15.960 --> 20:18.500
You're growing as a person.
I'm proud of you.

20:18.500 --> 20:21.710
Yeah. Cool.

20:21.710 --> 20:22.670
Pudding balloon.

20:22.670 --> 20:24.330
Is that slang?
What does that mean?

20:24.330 --> 20:26.620
No. I'm throwing
a pudding balloon at you.

20:26.620 --> 20:28.000
[ Grunts ]

20:28.000 --> 20:32.500
[ Laughs ]

20:32.500 --> 20:33.380
At least the things
you're throwing at me

20:33.380 --> 20:34.420
are getting softer.

20:34.420 --> 20:35.540
I appreciate that.

20:35.540 --> 20:36.620
[ Laughs ]

20:36.620 --> 20:38.750
Who cares how it happened?
We won!

20:38.750 --> 20:40.620
We're going on
a real-people vacation!

20:40.620 --> 20:41.960
[ Both chuckle ]

20:45.580 --> 20:50.710
♪♪

20:50.710 --> 20:55.580
♪♪

20:55.580 --> 20:56.500
[ Chuckles ]

20:58.460 --> 20:59.710
[ Chuckles ]

20:59.710 --> 21:03.380
♪♪

21:03.380 --> 21:05.000
All: [ Muffled ]
Now you should take

21:05.000 --> 21:06.710
the Anna-Kat Cookie Challenge!
